cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper deals with estimating content popularities from a traffic trace, which is a problem related to network measurements and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the problem of tuning content-level performance models, which involves statistical inference and optimization, suggesting that it could also fit in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Moreover, the paper mentions the use of Maximum Likelihood Estimation, which is a common statistical technique used in machine learning and data science, indicating that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
